# CODEOWNERS — require owner review for CI/CD and security-critical surfaces.
#
# `.github/` (workflows / Actions / Dependabot) is the highest-value target for
# supply-chain attacks ("poisoned pipeline execution"): one PR that rewrites a
# workflow can exfiltrate secrets / tokens. Gating it behind code-owner review
# mechanically blocks that class of attack. Takes effect once branch protection
# enables "Require review from Code Owners".
#
# Syntax: <pattern> <owner...>  — last match wins (most specific line applies).

# CI / GitHub Actions / Dependabot automation.
/.github/                @theosera

# CODEOWNERS itself (self-defense against tampering).
/.github/CODEOWNERS      @theosera

# Agent guardrails + security policy — weakening these weakens the whole posture.
/SECURITY.md             @theosera
/CLAUDE.md               @theosera
/CLAUDE.global.md        @theosera
/.claude/                @theosera

# Security boundary code: path containment + frontmatter field allowlist.
/src/pathSafety.ts       @theosera
/src/frontmatter.ts      @theosera
